N:npc-ml-agents
D:Train adaptive NPC behaviors with Unity ML-Agents and export ONNX models for runtime deployment. Use when defining observations and rewards, configuring PPO or SAC, running self-play or curriculum learning, and handing trained brains to unity-sentis.
G:unity ml-agents reinforcement-learning npc ppo sac onnx self-play curriculum sentis

U[5]:
  Train NPC behaviors instead of hand-authoring finite state machines
  Design observations, actions, rewards, and episode boundaries
  Run PPO or SAC training with TensorBoard monitoring
  Export ONNX checkpoints for Unity runtime deployment
  Connect trained models to unity-sentis for on-device inference

S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Install (pip install mlagents and add Unity ML-Agents package)
  2,Author-Agent (implement Agent, CollectObservations, OnActionReceived)
  3,Configure (set Behavior Parameters and trainer yaml)
  4,Train (run mlagents-learn and monitor results)
  5,Deploy (export ONNX and wire it into unity-sentis)

R[4]:
  Observation size must match Behavior Parameters exactly
  Reward shaping should reinforce the real objective, not shortcuts
  Export and test ONNX artifacts before deleting training checkpoints
  Keep runtime inference separate from the Python training stack

E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Navigation NPC","train an NPC to reach a target","PPO run produces ONNX checkpoint"
  "Competitive self-play","two-team combat arena","self-play ratings and checkpoints improve over time"
  "Runtime handoff","deploy trained policy","unity-sentis loads ONNX without Python runtime"
